76
00:03:25.665 --> 00:03:26.791
I think you did.

77
00:03:26.874 --> 00:03:29.460
It might have been me and I...
I don't know.

78
00:03:29.544 --> 00:03:31.384
No. I thought we did.
because there was that...

79
00:03:32.255 --> 00:03:34.674
What is... the Escher... the Escher drawing?

80
00:03:37.301 --> 00:03:38.678
The... With the...

81
00:03:39.387 --> 00:03:40.805
Gosh. I'm not gonna remember now.

82
00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:43.724
I remember talking about a hallway.

83
00:03:43.808 --> 00:03:46.519
But I do remember you
introducing the Escher drawing.

84
00:03:46.602 --> 00:03:47.603
Yeah.

85
00:03:48.688 --> 00:03:50.481
And it was... Yeah. go on.

86
00:03:50.565 --> 00:03:53.234
No. I can't remember how...
It might have been something that...

87
00:03:54.235 --> 00:03:59.198
I honestly can't remember if that was
something that Kyle and I found together

88
00:03:59.282 --> 00:04:01.826
or if we were talking about it
in the room. or...

89
00:04:01.909 --> 00:04:05.955
But it was just... It was one of those
really interesting drawings

90
00:04:06.038 --> 00:04:12.253
that just sort of felt very.
very otherworldly and multidimensional.

91
00:04:12.336 --> 00:04:16.340
And then just taking that
as the starting point.

92
00:04:16.424 --> 00:04:17.776
and then talking with you about it.

93
00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:23.055
and then getting Doug McCullough.
our production designer. involved.

94
00:04:23.139 --> 00:04:26.142
and. of course. J.Z. and his VFX team.

95
00:04:26.225 --> 00:04:29.312
And. like. it just...
As with everything on the show.

96
00:04:29.395 --> 00:04:34.192
it ended up being
such a collaborative effort from everyone.

97
00:04:34.817 --> 00:04:37.403
And then you... I want you to talk about.

98
00:04:37.487 --> 00:04:40.615
oh. my gosh. your directing template.

99
00:04:41.616 --> 00:04:45.703
I've not. like... You had pages of things
and they were color coded.

100
00:04:45.786 --> 00:04:48.664
and it was which world we're in
and where the camera needs to be.

101
00:04:48.748 --> 00:04:50.917
It was insa...
I've never seen anything like it.

102
00:04:51.459 --> 00:04:55.296
Well. it was fascinating because this...
you know. we'd shot the wall...

103
00:04:55.379 --> 00:04:57.798
the VR wall... the season before.

104
00:04:57.882 --> 00:04:59.842
And so. this was
our second season with it.

105
00:04:59.926 --> 00:05:03.054
and we'd gone through a whole season.
so this was the last episode with it.

106
00:05:03.137 --> 00:05:04.198
And the amount of knowledge

107
00:05:04.222 --> 00:05:08.518
we all accumulated on how to shoot it
has been astronomical.

108
00:05:10.269 --> 00:05:13.689
And it wasn't just us. the crew.
it was also the cast

109
00:05:13.773 --> 00:05:16.192
and what are they looking at.
and how to manage the wall...

110
00:05:16.275 --> 00:05:17.961
'cause the...
what the audience might not realize

111
00:05:17.985 --> 00:05:20.655
is while the wall seems
like it's all stable in those images. it...

112
00:05:20.738 --> 00:05:22.907
it's actually flying around
and moving around

113
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:24.630
- depending on where the camera...
- Yeah.

114
00:05:24.867 --> 00:05:26.869
So. while the cast...

115
00:05:26.953 --> 00:05:30.073
and. you know... and Sonequa and David
should speak about this in a little bit.

116
00:05:30.331 --> 00:05:35.628
but while the cast is looking at an image.
that image is not reality... total reality.

117
00:05:35.711 --> 00:05:38.714
Because reality is moving around them
like a carousel.

118
00:05:40.675 --> 00:05:44.845
And it was... it was quite involved.
the. you know.

119
00:05:44.929 --> 00:05:47.348
figuring out what world
is in which window.

120
00:05:47.431 --> 00:05:50.309
- you know. and all of that. and...
- Wow.

121
00:05:53.771 --> 00:05:55.356
It was definitely all of us working

122
00:05:56.482 --> 00:05:59.162
at the... our peak knowledge
of what the wall could and couldn't do.

123
00:06:01.153 --> 00:06:02.154
Wow.

124
00:06:02.238 --> 00:06:04.198
Remember this day. Tunde?

125
00:06:04.282 --> 00:06:06.701
I remember. I remember this day.

126
00:06:06.784 --> 00:06:08.911
- Tell us about this day.
- Yeah.

127
00:06:08.995 --> 00:06:11.455
I think it's got to be
one of the most intense...

128
00:06:13.124 --> 00:06:15.668
action. you know. sequences we've done.

129
00:06:16.294 --> 00:06:19.630
- One of 'em. For sure.
- Really. Yeah.

130
00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:22.425
And. I mean. this whole setup...

131
00:06:24.885 --> 00:06:27.179
it was a huge parking lot.

132
00:06:27.263 --> 00:06:32.143
I think across from the building
where the production offices were.

133
00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:35.062
- Right? Am I right about that?
- That's right.

134
00:06:35.146 --> 00:06:36.689
We took over the entire parking lot.

135
00:06:36.772 --> 00:06:39.483
The entire parking lot was this gigan...

136
00:06:39.567 --> 00:06:41.736
This monstrous rig.

137
00:06:41.819 --> 00:06:45.615
and so much of this is...
was just practical

138
00:06:45.698 --> 00:06:49.493
with this rain going

139
00:06:49.577 --> 00:06:51.120
and then with the wind machines.

140
00:06:51.203 --> 00:06:53.456
and then. I mean. it was intense.

141
00:06:53.539 --> 00:06:54.915
It was intense.

142
00:06:54.999 --> 00:06:56.125
I was... I was...

143
00:06:57.376 --> 00:07:00.379
I don't know. I was grateful
to have something like this.

144
00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:04.592
on the way out. you know? It was freezing.

145
00:07:05.092 --> 00:07:07.762
- I had so much padding underneath.
- Really?

146
00:07:07.845 --> 00:07:12.183
And there was always. like.
the danger of. like. hypothermia

147
00:07:12.266 --> 00:07:13.809
because there was so much waterlog

148
00:07:13.893 --> 00:07:16.437
with all of the freezing water.

149
00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:21.484
And. you know. I gotta big-up
the ladies in the costume department.

150
00:07:21.567 --> 00:07:24.904
because they really took
such good care of me.

151
00:07:24.987 --> 00:07:28.491
trying to change out each time
so that I wouldn't get sick.

152
00:07:31.077 --> 00:07:34.246
If I remember correctly.
they even heated the water for you.

153
00:07:34.330 --> 00:07:36.415
but by the time it came down
and it hit you.

154
00:07:36.499 --> 00:07:38.751
- it was cold again...
- Yeah. yeah!

155
00:07:38.834 --> 00:07:40.211
...because it was so cold on set.

156
00:07:40.294 --> 00:07:42.380
It was c... Yes. that's right. y'all.

157
00:07:42.463 --> 00:07:44.382
'cause we shot this
in November in Toronto.

158
00:07:44.465 --> 00:07:46.425
- Yes. it was Toronto. November.
- Oh. snap!

159
00:07:46.509 --> 00:07:47.510
Yeah!

160
00:07:48.636 --> 00:07:51.138
- Yeah. so it was freezing outside...
- Right.

161
00:07:51.222 --> 00:07:54.600
...and man. every single thing
that could have been done

162
00:07:54.684 --> 00:07:57.770
to. like. help the situation
was definitely done.

163
00:07:57.853 --> 00:07:59.998
Like. you know. but we were all
still just. like. tripping.

164
00:08:00.022 --> 00:08:03.025
Me and Tunde kept looking at each other.
being. like. "Yeah."

165
00:08:03.109 --> 00:08:05.069
- Right?
- Yeah. it was... it was nuts.

166
00:08:05.152 --> 00:08:08.614
because. you know. there are no visual
effects to the water that's falling here.

167
00:08:09.490 --> 00:08:11.367
- The water above the set. right?
- Really?

168
00:08:11.450 --> 00:08:13.953
So. Sonequa is actually in that water.

169
00:08:14.870 --> 00:08:17.206
And. yeah. Michelle's right.
It was heated.

170
00:08:17.289 --> 00:08:19.667
but the problem was.
by the time it got down to her.

171
00:08:19.750 --> 00:08:23.379
because it's falling 50 feet.
it was freezing. It was freezing.

172
00:08:23.462 --> 00:08:26.090
And so. I just want the audience to know.

173
00:08:26.173 --> 00:08:28.592
you know. when you're watching that.

174
00:08:28.676 --> 00:08:32.638
that is her operating
in freezing temperatures

175
00:08:33.264 --> 00:08:34.598
and doing a full-blown fight.

176
00:08:34.682 --> 00:08:36.058
It's one thing to do a fight.

177
00:08:36.142 --> 00:08:38.144
It's another thing to do a fight on wires.

178
00:08:38.227 --> 00:08:40.396
It's another thing to do a fight on wires

179
00:08:40.479 --> 00:08:42.773
with 50 mile per hour wind
blowing in your face.

180
00:08:42.857 --> 00:08:44.567
It's another thing to do a fight on wires

181
00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:47.027
with 50 mile per hour wind
blowing in your face

182
00:08:47.111 --> 00:08:50.740
with freezing water that's also
blowing in your face at that speed.

183
00:08:50.823 --> 00:08:53.909
So that was... Again. that's not
the kind of thing you could do

184
00:08:53.993 --> 00:08:54.994
just right out the gate.

185
00:08:55.077 --> 00:08:57.677
It's the kind of thing you'd have to do
with accumulated knowledge

186
00:08:58.622 --> 00:09:03.169
- of skill and talent and work ethic.
- Yeah.

187
00:09:03.669 --> 00:09:07.298
It's hard. That is hard work
that we saw that day.

188
00:09:08.132 --> 00:09:11.218
Thank you. and I mean.
Tunde is. like. everybody's producer.

189
00:09:11.302 --> 00:09:12.511
He's the producer's producer.

190
00:09:13.095 --> 00:09:15.765
He's the actor's producer.
He's the writer's producer.

191
00:09:15.848 --> 00:09:20.436
And so. he's such a... I don't know.
just such a phenomenal leader

192
00:09:20.519 --> 00:09:23.230
on set as well. and a guardian of sorts.

193
00:09:23.314 --> 00:09:26.609
And so.
you really feel like he's in it with you.

194
00:09:26.692 --> 00:09:28.235
And a lot of times. you are. Tunde.

195
00:09:28.319 --> 00:09:30.172
A lot of times.
you've literally been in it with us.

196
00:09:30.196 --> 00:09:32.531
- And so. it was... it was a lot of fun.
- Yeah.

197
00:09:33.824 --> 00:09:35.785
It really was. It was. like...

198
00:09:35.868 --> 00:09:37.548
I don't know.
I was really grateful for it.

199
00:09:39.038 --> 00:09:40.039
Yeah.

200
00:09:40.664 --> 00:09:41.832
And it's nice to...

201
00:09:41.916 --> 00:09:45.503
I think we're fortunate
that it's captured on film forever.

202
00:09:46.253 --> 00:09:47.254
Yeah.

203
00:09:47.338 --> 00:09:49.983
Yeah. because we went above and beyond.
You're right. Everybody did.

204
00:09:50.007 --> 00:09:52.218
Everybody went above and beyond
for that sequence. man.

205
00:09:52.301 --> 00:09:53.302
Yeah.

206
00:09:53.385 --> 00:09:55.471
- Look at her.
- Really cool.

207
00:09:55.554 --> 00:09:57.848
- Oh. my goodness.
- Eve Harlow.

208
00:09:57.932 --> 00:10:02.269
- Eve Harlow.
- What a great addition to this season.

209
00:10:02.353 --> 00:10:03.938
- Yeah.
- Like. truly. what a...

210
00:10:04.021 --> 00:10:07.399
I mean. casting-wise and producers.
and the powers that be.

211
00:10:07.483 --> 00:10:11.570
