when they hired Eve.

212
00:10:11.654 --> 00:10:15.032
I think she's just... she's a rocket.

213
00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:17.451
- She is.
- And a proper sweetheart.

214
00:10:18.077 --> 00:10:19.495
Yeah. she was one of those...

215
00:10:19.578 --> 00:10:22.248
You know. it happens
every now and then in casting

216
00:10:22.331 --> 00:10:23.332
where someone comes in

217
00:10:23.415 --> 00:10:28.587
and immediately. they explode
off the screen and you just know.

218
00:10:28.671 --> 00:10:30.756
"Oh. my gosh. That's the person."

219
00:10:30.840 --> 00:10:32.299
- And that was Eve...
- Yeah.

220
00:10:32.383 --> 00:10:36.929
And what was really funny is now. like.
meeting her as just a person.

221
00:10:37.012 --> 00:10:38.722
She's so... She's. like...

222
00:10:38.806 --> 00:10:41.517
She would be the first to say
she's not badass.

223
00:10:41.600 --> 00:10:45.437
She says of herself
that she's not badass. not coordinated.

224
00:10:45.521 --> 00:10:47.773
She was so nervous about doing the stunts.

225
00:10:47.857 --> 00:10:50.568
She's. like. just the nicest. gentlest.

226
00:10:50.651 --> 00:10:54.446
- like. sweet. animal-loving person...
- Yes!

227
00:10:54.530 --> 00:10:57.032
...and she plays this total badass.

228
00:10:57.116 --> 00:10:59.910
you know.
who wants to kick your ass in this.

229
00:10:59.994 --> 00:11:00.995
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

230
00:11:01.078 --> 00:11:02.162
Talk about work ethic.

231
00:11:02.246 --> 00:11:06.333
Man. she really stepped up to the plate.

232
00:11:06.417 --> 00:11:10.004
and it's a testament
to her skill as an actor.

233
00:11:10.087 --> 00:11:14.466
How different she is in real life.

234
00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:16.135
We were all. just. so proud of her.

235
00:11:16.218 --> 00:11:18.554
and she was proud of herself as well.

236
00:11:18.637 --> 00:11:20.097
'cause she surprised herself.

237
00:11:20.723 --> 00:11:23.100
She saw just what she was capable of.

238
00:11:23.767 --> 00:11:25.436
- Exactly.
- Yeah. Isn't that the truth?

239
00:11:25.519 --> 00:11:26.520
Isn't that the truth?

240
00:11:26.604 --> 00:11:28.147
Yeah. and she came in.

241
00:11:28.230 --> 00:11:33.277
and it's a thing to have to go toe-to-toe
with Michael Burnham...

242
00:11:36.363 --> 00:11:39.325
and to be a formidable force
in the face of Michael Burnham.

243
00:11:39.408 --> 00:11:41.785
And so. it was really important
to all of us

244
00:11:41.869 --> 00:11:45.831
that Michael go up against somebody

245
00:11:45.915 --> 00:11:47.625
that. you know.

246
00:11:47.708 --> 00:11:51.712
we feel is a close match.

247
00:11:51.795 --> 00:11:54.214
and I thought
she really pulled it off well.

248
00:11:54.298 --> 00:11:58.594
And I think she did something that.
hopefully. she's proud of too.

249
00:11:58.677 --> 00:12:00.095
Yeah. Yeah.

250
00:12:00.179 --> 00:12:02.723
It's no small feat
for any actor to come in

251
00:12:02.806 --> 00:12:07.269
and share the screen with both of you.

252
00:12:07.353 --> 00:12:09.438
Like. that's. you know. that's just.

253
00:12:09.521 --> 00:12:11.941
that is not an easy thing to do.

254
00:12:12.858 --> 00:12:15.027
So. yeah. she did great.

255
00:12:15.110 --> 00:12:17.529
And so did Elias. because he had to...

256
00:12:17.613 --> 00:12:20.407
- Yeah.
- Elias Toufexis. my goodness.

257
00:12:20.491 --> 00:12:24.745
Who came back to us
after such a long time.

258
00:12:25.704 --> 00:12:30.417
