344
00:16:42.753 --> 00:16:44.630
Oh. man. Yeah.

345
00:16:44.713 --> 00:16:46.590
- Look at that.
- And it was real. real fire.

346
00:16:46.673 --> 00:16:48.050
It was real hot.

347
00:16:48.133 --> 00:16:50.552
Like. you would have to step out
after each take

348
00:16:50.636 --> 00:16:53.430
because it would get hard to breathe
from the smoke.

349
00:16:53.972 --> 00:16:55.909
- Yeah. it was...
- That was also done in the parking lot.

350
00:16:55.933 --> 00:16:57.368
It was also done in the parking lot.

351
00:16:57.392 --> 00:17:00.604
Yeah. it was about 100 yards
from where the rain scene was done.

352
00:17:03.232 --> 00:17:04.858
This one fell on the same day.

353
00:17:04.942 --> 00:17:07.611
They were two separate days. but get this.

354
00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:08.880
- This is a good question.
- Right. Of course.

355
00:17:08.904 --> 00:17:11.490
The rain scene was only done
on the second half of the day.

356
00:17:11.573 --> 00:17:13.575
- We only had seven hours to shoot it...
- Yes.

357
00:17:13.659 --> 00:17:16.912
...and the fire scene was also done
on the second half of the day.

358
00:17:16.995 --> 00:17:17.996
Wow.

359
00:17:19.873 --> 00:17:23.877
Think of. like. what the crew was doing.

360
00:17:25.212 --> 00:17:26.338
I can only imagine.

361
00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:28.840
Yes. that one big day.

362
00:17:28.924 --> 00:17:32.970
And I gotta big-up Anita
