"It's too hard. We can't do it."

381
00:18:39.119 --> 00:18:42.331
The answer is always.
"Okay. How do we do that?

382
00:18:42.414 --> 00:18:44.875
- And how do we make it safe?"
- Yeah.

383
00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:47.544
"But how do we make it epic and awesome.

384
00:18:47.627 --> 00:18:51.173
and bigger than we even
think it can be done?"

385
00:18:51.256 --> 00:18:52.257
- Right.
- Yeah.

386
00:18:52.341 --> 00:18:55.302
I think that fire sce... Didn't we get...
Didn't we get a call for a...

387
00:18:55.385 --> 00:18:57.763
Like. didn't someone call in
from a plane or something?

388
00:18:57.846 --> 00:18:59.657
- The fire department?
- Yeah. from the... from the...

389
00:18:59.681 --> 00:19:02.851
Yeah. from the main city. from downtown.

390
00:19:02.934 --> 00:19:04.061
Yeah. downtown.

391
00:19:04.144 --> 00:19:06.980
Yeah. and they thought that there was
a massive fire happening.

392
00:19:07.064 --> 00:19:08.899
you know. down by the river over there.

393
00:19:08.982 --> 00:19:10.542
Yeah. and the fire department showed up

394
00:19:11.568 --> 00:19:14.363
and was gonna shut us down
and then they realized there was a permit

395
00:19:14.446 --> 00:19:17.657
and that it was safe and.
you know. we showed them the things

396
00:19:17.741 --> 00:19:20.077
- and it was okay. you know.
- Right.

397
00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:23.497
Look at these two
absolutely brilliant actors.

398
00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:26.041
- Yeah.
- Look at that one over there.

399
00:19:26.124 --> 00:19:28.543
Who's that guy that's in the scene?

400
00:19:28.627 --> 00:19:29.920
Ajala.

401
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:32.172
Who's that brilliant actor?

402
00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:35.023
- Look at these men.
- There he is again.

403
00:19:35.884 --> 00:19:38.637
- Look at Blu. I tell you...
- Big-up. Blu.

404
00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:42.891
- The talent... The talent and the craft.
- Yes.

405
00:19:42.974 --> 00:19:45.727
- Yeah.
- It just worked with all of you.

406
00:19:45.811 --> 00:19:47.854
- It really does.
- Yeah.

407
00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:54.194
And the camera work.
the camera movement. the directing.

408
00:19:54.277 --> 00:19:55.946
- just a shout-out to that too.
- Yeah.

409
00:19:56.029 --> 00:19:59.366
Like. there's so much energy

410
00:19:59.449 --> 00:20:02.119
in what all of you are doing
in every scene

411
00:20:02.202 --> 00:20:05.038
and in the emotion and intensity

412
00:20:05.122 --> 00:20:07.791
and attention
that you're giving to one another

413
00:20:07.874 --> 00:20:09.709
and to what's happening in the story.

414
00:20:09.793 --> 00:20:14.089
And. you know.
all of that is highlighted by Tunde.

415
00:20:14.172 --> 00:20:18.760
what you and your team are doing
with the camera and the movement of it.

416
00:20:18.844 --> 00:20:21.847
and where you're putting it.
and just the slight motion back and forth.

417
00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:26.476
It all... And it comes together
in just a really. really wonderful way.

418
00:20:27.894 --> 00:20:32.941
Yeah. The camera team
led by Phil Lanyon was exquisite.

419
00:20:33.608 --> 00:20:37.028
And Michael Carr is the operator
behind the lens here.

420
00:20:40.907 --> 00:20:42.492
It takes a lot. because...

421
00:20:44.327 --> 00:20:46.872
when the actors are outputting this much.

422
00:20:46.955 --> 00:20:50.917
you need someone behind the lens
that isn't going to miss it. right?

423
00:20:51.001 --> 00:20:53.462
And is gonna be in tune with
what's happening emotionally.

424
00:20:54.463 --> 00:20:56.298
Because I'm an emotional-based director.

425
00:20:56.381 --> 00:21:00.302
it all comes from. what emotion
am I trying to put in the audience's mind

426
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:03.013
in the moment where maybe
it didn't exist before.

427
00:21:03.597 --> 00:21:06.141
And every inch matters.

428
00:21:06.224 --> 00:21:12.063
And it's really comforting to have someone
that's handling those lights

429
00:21:12.147 --> 00:21:14.274
and someone who's behind that camera.

430
00:21:14.357 --> 00:21:17.819
who is in sync
with what the cast is doing.

431
00:21:19.779 --> 00:21:22.240
Yeah. I feel like when...
when there isn't. like...

432
00:21:22.324 --> 00:21:26.578
I've. you know. seen things before
