1254
01:03:59.545 --> 01:04:01.422
Oh. Oded.

1255
01:04:01.505 --> 01:04:04.967
Oh. goodness. How much do we love him?

1256
01:04:05.051 --> 01:04:07.136
- He really...
- Yeah. what a guy.

1257
01:04:07.219 --> 01:04:11.932
Talk about real and true and raw
and weighted. and...

1258
01:04:13.601 --> 01:04:18.355
I just... I adore his work on...
and him as well.

1259
01:04:18.439 --> 01:04:19.774
What a lovely man.

1260
01:04:19.857 --> 01:04:20.858
He is.

1261
01:04:21.358 --> 01:04:24.153
I feel like we've cast
all of the characters

1262
01:04:24.236 --> 01:04:27.323
as leaders that we would want to be
our actual leaders...

1263
01:04:27.406 --> 01:04:28.699
- Yes!
- ...in the world.

1264
01:04:29.742 --> 01:04:32.369
That's such a great way
to describe it. Michelle.

1265
01:04:35.623 --> 01:04:38.375
Yeah. everybody is just... I just...

1266
01:04:40.211 --> 01:04:41.587
It's just... It's phenomenal

1267
01:04:41.670 --> 01:04:44.131
to be able to watch all of these people
do what they do

1268
01:04:44.215 --> 01:04:45.966
and learn from them.

1269
01:04:46.592 --> 01:04:50.971
I also gotta big-up Teresa Buccione
who was the head of our hair department

1270
01:04:51.055 --> 01:04:54.266
here at the tail end of <i>Discovery.</i>

1271
01:04:54.350 --> 01:04:56.328
And Craig-Ryan French.
head of our makeup department.

1272
01:04:56.352 --> 01:04:57.895
- but the...
- Yes.

1273
01:04:58.479 --> 01:05:03.567
Right? Because look. we really went in
on these intricate. like. styles.

1274
01:05:03.651 --> 01:05:08.781
these. like. Black. ethnic.
African-inspired styles.

1275
01:05:08.864 --> 01:05:10.783
- I was so happy to do it.
- Right?

1276
01:05:10.866 --> 01:05:12.034
Yeah.

1277
01:05:12.743 --> 01:05:13.744
Beautiful.

1278
01:05:14.578 --> 01:05:19.458
Yeah. it was interesting what you guys
were saying about... about the cast.

1279
01:05:19.542 --> 01:05:21.377
And. you know.
growing up watching <i>Star Trek.</i>

1280
01:05:21.460 --> 01:05:26.715
I always felt like. okay... I was going
through my own thing as a kid and...

1281
01:05:27.299 --> 01:05:29.885
But the people on <i>Star Trek</i>
would be my friends.

1282
01:05:29.969 --> 01:05:32.012
Like I... Like on <i>TNG.</i>

1283
01:05:32.096 --> 01:05:35.015
like. I could see myself. like.
hanging out with them. you know.

1284
01:05:36.016 --> 01:05:37.726
or going on adventures with them.

1285
01:05:37.810 --> 01:05:40.729
And what was wonderful about <i>Discovery</i>
is I think that got achieved again

1286
01:05:40.813 --> 01:05:43.816
for the next generation.
or for people like...

1287
01:05:43.899 --> 01:05:47.278
I believe that I could hang out
and be friends with them. you know.

1288
01:05:47.361 --> 01:05:50.239
and that they would be good people.
you know. and accept me.

1289
01:05:52.992 --> 01:05:56.871
I think... I hope... I hope that there's
people watching who feel the same way.

1290
01:05:56.954 --> 01:05:58.956
Yeah. Me too.

1291
01:06:01.083 --> 01:06:02.376
- This...
- This is such a...

1292
01:06:02.459 --> 01:06:04.146
This... Look how be... Oh. sorry. Michelle.

1293
01:06:04.170 --> 01:06:06.630
No. I was just...
I was gonna say it's beautiful.

1294
01:06:06.714 --> 01:06:09.967
I'm not gonna have Tunde
tell the story of the sun.

1295
01:06:10.050 --> 01:06:13.637
but I will say it was very cold this day.
very cold.

1296
01:06:13.721 --> 01:06:16.307
- You two were troupers. by the way.
- It was very cold.

1297
01:06:16.390 --> 01:06:20.186
Both of you out there acting as though
you're just perfectly comfortable...

1298
01:06:20.269 --> 01:06:22.354
- Right? Right?
- ...and it's freezing and below.

1299
01:06:24.190 --> 01:06:26.525
- Yeah. the runny noses.
- This is some acting right here.

1300
01:06:27.067 --> 01:06:28.277
Teary eyes. I remember that.

1301
01:06:28.360 --> 01:06:30.487
Me and David have been
through the elements. man.

1302
01:06:30.571 --> 01:06:33.073
- But yeah. it was fro...
- Yeah.

1303
01:06:33.908 --> 01:06:36.744
We were trying so hard
not to let our teeth chatter.

1304
01:06:36.827 --> 01:06:38.120
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1305
01:06:38.204 --> 01:06:40.414
You guys did a great job.
You wouldn't know.

1306
01:06:40.915 --> 01:06:42.208
- No.
- Yes.

1307
01:06:42.291 --> 01:06:43.417
Yeah. it was okay...

1308
01:06:43.500 --> 01:06:45.920
Didn't we start this
at. like. 5:00 in the morning?

1309
01:06:46.003 --> 01:06:47.296
Yeah.

1310
01:06:47.379 --> 01:06:48.440
The moment the cast is called.

1311
01:06:48.464 --> 01:06:50.841
- people are coming out with jackets.
- Yeah. Yeah.

1312
01:06:51.425 --> 01:06:53.177
Yeah. like those warm coats.

1313
01:06:53.260 --> 01:06:55.304
We... I had the HotShots everywhere.

1314
01:06:56.180 --> 01:06:57.556
Yeah.

1315
01:06:57.640 --> 01:07:00.893
So directors. film students watching.
just remember that

1316
01:07:00.976 --> 01:07:03.312
when you go into the elements.
it's easy to forget...

1317
01:07:03.395 --> 01:07:05.332
because you're just.
you're intent on the image...

1318
01:07:05.356 --> 01:07:06.899
But when you go into the elements.

1319
01:07:06.982 --> 01:07:09.735
you and the crew can put
layers upon layers. upon layers on

1320
01:07:09.818 --> 01:07:12.446
to keep yourselves warm
indefinitely through the day. right?

1321
01:07:12.529 --> 01:07:16.325
There's no excuse not to be
at least sort of warm through the day.

1322
01:07:16.408 --> 01:07:17.848
I mean. there's a couple of excuses.

1323
01:07:17.910 --> 01:07:21.038
But the cast. they got to wear
what they gotta wear on camera.

1324
01:07:21.121 --> 01:07:25.668
so they're exposed. you know.
so it's just something to think about.

1325
01:07:25.751 --> 01:07:28.295
Not only getting them out there.
but what's the whole logistics

1326
01:07:28.379 --> 01:07:30.214
around trying to keep them warm?

1327
01:07:30.297 --> 01:07:32.049
And there's gonna be some success rates

1328
01:07:32.132 --> 01:07:34.969
and some that are not so successful
in accomplishing that.

1329
01:07:35.052 --> 01:07:37.513
But it's something
that a lot of thought needs to go into

1330
01:07:37.596 --> 01:07:39.723
when you... when you shoot in the elements.

1331
01:07:40.724 --> 01:07:44.270
One thing about this scene here...

1332
01:07:44.937 --> 01:07:48.399
Because we didn't know
it was gonna be our last season.

1333
01:07:48.482 --> 01:07:51.735
the shot coming up where they
kind of walk off into the sunset

1334
01:07:51.819 --> 01:07:55.072
was originally going to be
the end of the season.

1335
01:07:55.155 --> 01:07:57.366
And then we were gonna come back
for another season.

1336
01:07:57.449 --> 01:08:00.369
When we found out that. much later...

1337
01:08:00.452 --> 01:08:02.871
We were editing. I think. episodes 8 and 9

1338
01:08:02.955 --> 01:08:06.750
at the time that we found out
that this was gonna be our final season.

1339
01:08:07.251 --> 01:08:08.460
We had to go back.

1340
01:08:09.336 --> 01:08:11.231
And people have asked.
did you have to change anything

1341
01:08:11.255 --> 01:08:13.424
