how do you make 'em look older.

1402
01:12:03.111 --> 01:12:05.781
and yet beautiful
and distinguished. right?

1403
01:12:06.949 --> 01:12:09.034
What's that balance in the alchemy?

1404
01:12:09.117 --> 01:12:11.787
Pardon the pun. because the name
of his company is Alchemy.

1405
01:12:11.870 --> 01:12:15.624
But what's that alchemy in how
thin or thick those prosthetics should be.

1406
01:12:15.707 --> 01:12:18.794
and I thought they did
a great job with them.

1407
01:12:18.877 --> 01:12:21.296
And that and the hair and the makeup
and just...

1408
01:12:21.380 --> 01:12:22.506
Yeah.

1409
01:12:22.589 --> 01:12:23.924
Yeah.

1410
01:12:24.007 --> 01:12:26.552
Yeah. it was a team...
As everything is. right?

1411
01:12:26.635 --> 01:12:29.179
As we've been saying.
as we always say. you know.

1412
01:12:29.263 --> 01:12:32.224
- it was such a team effort.
- Yeah.

1413
01:12:32.307 --> 01:12:33.392
Man.

1414
01:12:33.475 --> 01:12:34.643
- And it's hard.
- It's...

1415
01:12:34.726 --> 01:12:35.811
I'm sorry. go on.

1416
01:12:35.894 --> 01:12:37.771
No. you go. you go.

1417
01:12:37.854 --> 01:12:39.398
I was just gonna say it was...

1418
01:12:39.481 --> 01:12:42.192
You know. you had said something
a couple of years ago. Sonequa.

1419
01:12:42.276 --> 01:12:45.946
about when something emotional
is going on in your life.

1420
01:12:46.029 --> 01:12:48.907
it affects your creative instrument.

1421
01:12:49.491 --> 01:12:50.659
And you have to work harder

1422
01:12:50.742 --> 01:12:53.704
to make sure your creative instrument's
working in the right direction.

1423
01:12:53.787 --> 01:12:55.723
And that's what I was experiencing
when I came back.

1424
01:12:55.747 --> 01:12:59.251
I actually didn't want to come back
to do this. because I was...

1425
01:12:59.334 --> 01:13:01.211
I came up with all these reasons
in my mind.

1426
01:13:01.295 --> 01:13:04.381
but really the main reason was
how emotional I knew it would be.

1427
01:13:04.965 --> 01:13:07.551
And I don't like being that emotional.
you know.

1428
01:13:07.634 --> 01:13:11.179
like to the point where
my creative instrument is not working.

1429
01:13:11.263 --> 01:13:12.514
it's not functioning correctly.

1430
01:13:12.598 --> 01:13:15.225
where I have to keep checking myself
and checking myself.

1431
01:13:15.309 --> 01:13:18.729
And things that would ordinarily be.
instinctually. "This is how to do it."

1432
01:13:18.812 --> 01:13:21.064
now take two or three times to get there.

1433
01:13:21.607 --> 01:13:24.818
And that was what I was experiencing
while directing these.

1434
01:13:27.696 --> 01:13:29.740
That deer. I love that deer.

1435
01:13:33.410 --> 01:13:35.287
Me too. and the sound it makes.

1436
01:13:36.163 --> 01:13:38.915
Oh. my goodness. Sawan.

1437
01:13:42.169 --> 01:13:44.671
He looks like he could be your son.

1438
01:13:44.755 --> 01:13:48.675
The picture of the three of you together
is just fantastic.

1439
01:13:49.676 --> 01:13:50.802
This is it.

1440
01:13:50.886 --> 01:13:55.223
And. you know. speaking of having
a big job ahead of him.

1441
01:13:55.307 --> 01:13:56.975
like a lot of us. you know. do.

1442
01:13:57.059 --> 01:13:58.769
I mean. my goodness.

1443
01:13:58.852 --> 01:14:04.566
It's like. "Look. You're the legacy.
You're the legacy bearer." you know?

1444
01:14:05.734 --> 01:14:08.236
That's the theme of this. right.

1445
01:14:08.320 --> 01:14:13.617
is the legacy of these characters
and also of this ship and this crew.

1446
01:14:13.700 --> 01:14:16.078
And it's like. "You hold that."

1447
01:14:16.620 --> 01:14:19.665
And he just held it so well.

1448
01:14:19.748 --> 01:14:26.129
He was so brilliant and so kind
and giving and engaged and fun

1449
01:14:26.213 --> 01:14:30.801
and everything you could have asked for
and more.

1450
01:14:30.884 --> 01:14:33.303
And we just had a blast together.

1451
01:14:33.387 --> 01:14:38.350
and we bonded... all of us bonded with him
so quickly and so easily

1452
01:14:38.433 --> 01:14:41.019
that it was super sad to say bye to him.

1453
01:14:41.103 --> 01:14:43.772
- It was as if he had always been with us.
- Yeah.

1454
01:14:43.855 --> 01:14:46.233
David. are you still not watching?

1455
01:14:46.942 --> 01:14:49.027
Yeah. I can't. I can't.

1456
01:14:49.903 --> 01:14:51.405
I can't. but I'm here.

1457
01:14:51.488 --> 01:14:54.324
I'm listening to everything. but I can't.

1458
01:14:54.408 --> 01:14:56.410
He said. "I can't. I can't."

1459
01:14:57.369 --> 01:14:58.954
- I love it.
- Nah. it's my heart.

1460
01:14:59.037 --> 01:15:00.330
- It's... Yeah.
- I hear you.

1461
01:15:00.414 --> 01:15:03.709
It was such a joy filming this.
but I can't watch it. I can't.

1462
01:15:03.792 --> 01:15:05.127
Yeah. I hear you.

1463
01:15:05.794 --> 01:15:08.088
You know. Tunde. something you said
makes me think about

1464
01:15:08.171 --> 01:15:11.591
when you talk about the emotionality
you might be going through in your life

1465
01:15:11.675 --> 01:15:13.361
and how it affects
your creative instrument.

1466
01:15:13.385 --> 01:15:16.555
because I had a little bit of that too
over the course of this season

1467
01:15:16.638 --> 01:15:22.227
from the storyline with the Progenitors
and finding the technology and everything.

1468
01:15:22.310 --> 01:15:25.439
And I just remember. Michelle.

1469
01:15:25.522 --> 01:15:27.983
when you and I spoke about the season
before we came in.

1470
01:15:28.066 --> 01:15:30.736
and you told me that. you know.
what we would find

1471
01:15:30.819 --> 01:15:32.946
is that the Progenitors
found this technology.

1472
01:15:33.029 --> 01:15:34.906
that they don't know where it came from.

1473
01:15:35.490 --> 01:15:39.077
I remember. you know.
I was super grateful for that.

1474
01:15:39.161 --> 01:15:44.124
And it's another reason why it's amazing
how everything ended up turning out...

1475
01:15:44.207 --> 01:15:47.836
this episode in particular...
because it just continues to...

1476
01:15:47.919 --> 01:15:52.090
Even Burnham's captain's log.

1477
01:15:52.174 --> 01:15:56.303
it just leaves the door open
for every kind of possibility.

1478
01:15:57.888 --> 01:16:00.599
And I love that we end it that way.

1479
01:16:01.767 --> 01:16:04.895
where it's like. "Hey. look.
it can continue to look up and out.

1480
01:16:04.978 --> 01:16:06.521
It could be anything." you know?

1481
01:16:07.272 --> 01:16:10.776
Anything is still possible.

1482
01:16:11.276 --> 01:16:12.360
Thought that was beautiful.

1483
01:16:12.444 --> 01:16:15.030
That actually came from you. by the way.

1484
01:16:15.614 --> 01:16:20.160
'Cause when we pitched the season to you

1485
01:16:20.243 --> 01:16:22.078
at the very. very beginning. before...

1486
01:16:22.162 --> 01:16:26.416
Like. very early. we sort of pitched you
the. "Here's where season 5 is going."

1487
01:16:26.500 --> 01:16:27.959
and we talked about the Progenitors.

1488
01:16:28.043 --> 01:16:31.797
and I just remember you saying.
"Well. they won't be the"...

1489
01:16:31.880 --> 01:16:33.298
I can't remember how you put it.

1490
01:16:33.381 --> 01:16:36.635
but it was. "They won't be
the be-all. end-all." right?

1491
01:16:36.718 --> 01:16:37.928
Yeah. That's right.

1492
01:16:38.011 --> 01:16:40.180
And that really...

1493
01:16:40.263 --> 01:16:42.390
You saying that really struck me.

1494
01:16:42.474 --> 01:16:46.770
like. "Of course. they can't be
the be-all. end-all." It has to be...

1495
01:16:46.853 --> 01:16:51.274
Like. you have to leave
the many possibilities for all the things.

1496
01:16:51.358 --> 01:16:54.444
So that came. actually.
out of that conversation with you

1497
01:16:54.528 --> 01:16:56.863
and honoring that with you.

1498
01:16:56.947 --> 01:16:58.156
And it felt very important.

1499
01:16:58.240 --> 01:17:00.742
And it's a hundred percent
the right choice.

1500
01:17:00.826 --> 01:17:03.620
You wouldn't want to say that that was it

1501
01:17:03.703 --> 01:17:06.957
and that they were. you know.
creators with a capital C.

1502
01:17:07.040 --> 01:17:08.667
because you wanna leave it open.

1503
01:17:12.045 --> 01:17:13.839
I didn't know that. Michelle.

1504
01:17:14.589 --> 01:17:15.590
Yeah.

1505
01:17:15.674 --> 01:17:16.967
I didn't know that.

1506
01:17:22.013 --> 01:17:25.851
Part of this...
I think part of this conversation here

1507
01:17:25.934 --> 01:17:28.979
was originally between Burnham and Book.

1508
01:17:29.062 --> 01:17:31.898
that we thought of... that previous scene...
to put it in with this.

1509
01:17:31.982 --> 01:17:33.733
This was...

1510
01:17:33.817 --> 01:17:36.820
This whole ending coda sequence

1511
01:17:36.903 --> 01:17:41.825
was really interesting
in terms of figuring out how to do it.

1512
01:17:41.908 --> 01:17:44.369
'cause. you know. we had a limited time.

1513
01:17:44.452 --> 01:17:46.788
We knew we were gonna have
three days to shoot.

1514
01:17:47.372 --> 01:17:49.040
Some of the sets were already gone.

1515
01:17:49.124 --> 01:17:52.460
We knew that we were only
gonna be able to get certain actors.

1516
01:17:52.544 --> 01:17:55.547
and. logistically.
getting everybody in the next scene

1517
01:17:55.630 --> 01:17:59.009
to be there on a particular day
so we could have a goodbye.

1518
01:17:59.092 --> 01:18:04.890
And. you know. Kyle and Alex and I
really just kind of worked through it.

1519
01:18:04.973 --> 01:18:10.604
and. you know. it was no small feat
to try and figure it out.

1520
01:18:10.687 --> 01:18:12.772
But I really love what we came up with.

1521
01:18:12.856 --> 01:18:15.317
and then what you all do on the screen.

1522
01:18:15.400 --> 01:18:19.112
and Tunde bringing it to life.
and everybody. you know?

1523
01:18:19.195 --> 01:18:21.823
It's everyone's passion
bringing it all together.

1524
01:18:23.283 --> 01:18:27.996
I hope people feel really good about it
when they finally watch this

1525
01:18:28.079 --> 01:18:30.081
and get to see the way it ends.

1526
01:18:31.333 --> 01:18:37.172
I love the way that last scene
with Burnham and Leto was written.

1527
01:18:37.255 --> 01:18:39.341
and the fact that his name is Leto.
it was just...

1528
01:18:39.424 --> 01:18:42.719
- Yeah. Yeah.
- ...beautiful. beautiful. beautiful.

1529
01:18:44.095 --> 01:18:46.473
And now. of course.
here they're taking off the A.

1530
01:18:46.556 --> 01:18:49.434
I think people will probably notice
that the DOTs are taking off the A.

1531
01:18:49.517 --> 01:18:53.063
'cause we're about to...
we have to make it match "Calypso."

1532
01:18:53.146 --> 01:18:55.106
which was just the 1031

1533
01:18:55.190 --> 01:18:57.192
that didn't have an A
when it went out there.

1534
01:18:57.275 --> 01:18:59.319
Look at that. Easter egg.

1535
01:18:59.402 --> 01:19:00.612
Easter egg. yeah.

1536
01:19:03.740 --> 01:19:04.741
Look at that great shot.

1537
01:19:05.575 --> 01:19:07.786
Wow. And I also. you know...

1538
01:19:07.869 --> 01:19:09.788
I'm a little bit ahead of it.

1539
01:19:09.871 --> 01:19:13.875
but I got to big-up Robinne.
Robinne Fanfair.

1540
01:19:13.959 --> 01:19:19.714
who voiced Zora for us
when we were there on set.

1541
01:19:19.798 --> 01:19:23.885
She had such an interesting process
that I really respected

1542
01:19:23.969 --> 01:19:27.472
because she didn't watch.
she just listened.

1543
01:19:27.555 --> 01:19:29.474
She would be in her chair
with her headphones.

1544
01:19:29.557 --> 01:19:31.726
and she would just go off of...

1545
01:19:31.810 --> 01:19:34.354
It was just like a sort of
audio experience for her.

1546
01:19:34.896 --> 01:19:38.274
because she felt that
that was the case for Zora. and so...

1547
01:19:38.900 --> 01:19:41.820
or somehow she felt
that it connected her more to Zora.

1548
01:19:41.903 --> 01:19:43.905
And then we have someone else
who comes in.

1549
01:19:43.989 --> 01:19:46.992
So there's two people
who are Zora essentially.

1550
01:19:47.075 --> 01:19:48.118
Yeah.

1551
01:19:48.201 --> 01:19:51.913
But she's the one who would voice for us
when we were there in Toronto.

1552
01:19:51.997 --> 01:19:54.582
It was lovely to watch her work.

1553
01:19:54.666 --> 01:19:58.086
- Yeah. Annabelle is our Zora voice in...
- Yeah.

1554
01:19:58.169 --> 01:20:01.297
And. yeah. Robinne... it was interesting
that you mentioned that. Sonequa.

1555
01:20:01.381 --> 01:20:06.177
because I went to do a private blocking
on a particular scene...

1556
01:20:06.261 --> 01:20:07.512
I forget which one it was...

1557
01:20:07.595 --> 01:20:09.931
and Zora was talking a lot
in that particular scene.

1558
01:20:10.015 --> 01:20:14.019
And I tried to get Robinne to come
and join the private rehearsal.

1559
01:20:14.102 --> 01:20:15.729
but she didn't want to.

1560
01:20:15.812 --> 01:20:16.855
And I was like...

1561
01:20:16.938 --> 01:20:20.025
And I wasn't sure about
what that reluctance was.

1562
01:20:20.108 --> 01:20:22.777
Now you've just answered
that question for me.

1563
01:20:22.861 --> 01:20:25.113
- So. you know. thank you for that.
- Yeah.

1564
01:20:25.655 --> 01:20:28.199
Yeah. She felt like somehow
it would help her

1565
01:20:28.283 --> 01:20:34.748
get into the sort of. you know.
artificial mindset of Zora.

1566
01:20:34.831 --> 01:20:37.375
just having it be an audio experience.

1567
01:20:37.459 --> 01:20:39.753
She was so giving and there.

1568
01:20:39.836 --> 01:20:41.921
and I really felt. you know...

1569
01:20:42.005 --> 01:20:45.717
I really felt the life
when I would be with her there in Toronto.

1570
01:20:45.800 --> 01:20:47.635
So I was grateful for her.

1571
01:20:48.845 --> 01:20:49.971
I love this part.

1572
01:20:51.264 --> 01:20:53.058
Tunde. It's a Tunde special.

1573
01:20:54.976 --> 01:20:55.977
Yeah.

1574
01:20:57.812 --> 01:21:01.816
Yeah. this was a difficult scene to shoot
for a variety of reasons.

1575
01:21:01.900 --> 01:21:05.487
Not logistically or. you know...
but just emotionally.

1576
01:21:06.279 --> 01:21:08.073
You wanna get it right. right?

1577
01:21:08.573 --> 01:21:09.616
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1578
01:21:11.951 --> 01:21:14.245
Yeah.
you knocked it out of the park. Tunde.

1579
01:21:14.329 --> 01:21:15.330
Yeah.

1580
01:21:15.955 --> 01:21:21.127
And I love that
everyone was able to come back.

1581
01:21:21.920 --> 01:21:25.173
Wilson was not.
'cause he was working on something

1582
01:21:25.256 --> 01:21:27.136
- at the time.
- On the other side of the world.

1583
01:21:27.175 --> 01:21:28.218
Yeah.

1584
01:21:29.677 --> 01:21:34.015
But we were able to.
through the magic of editing.

1585
01:21:34.099 --> 01:21:35.433
make it seem like he was there.

1586
01:21:35.517 --> 01:21:38.394
We had a great Wilson stunt double...

1587
01:21:38.478 --> 01:21:39.979
not stunt double. body double.

1588
01:21:40.063 --> 01:21:41.314
Stunt double.

1589
01:21:42.065 --> 01:21:43.066
Body double.

1590
01:21:44.776 --> 01:21:47.737
So as we come back here.

1591
01:21:47.821 --> 01:21:52.742
we'll see him. and he's not...
that's not actually him.

1592
01:21:53.952 --> 01:21:55.161
I got to say. too. Michelle.

1593
01:21:55.245 --> 01:21:58.748
I know we appreciate CBS
and Paramount+ for getting us up here.

1594
01:21:58.832 --> 01:22:01.376
but I also just have to say

1595
01:22:01.459 --> 01:22:04.921
that you just astounded me
with this script for this coda.

1596
01:22:06.464 --> 01:22:09.008
Because. you know. I know you and Alex.

1597
01:22:09.092 --> 01:22:12.137
you were campaigning for us
and fighting for us

1598
01:22:12.220 --> 01:22:14.305
and they were gracious to us.

1599
01:22:14.389 --> 01:22:18.268
but you did this in two minutes
with two pages. you know.

1600
01:22:19.811 --> 01:22:25.483
and I will always be floored
by what you were able to do.

1601
01:22:25.567 --> 01:22:27.235
- Thank you.
- Yeah. Yeah.

1602
01:22:29.821 --> 01:22:30.989
So neat.

1603
01:22:32.031 --> 01:22:34.993
Emily and Oyin. oh. my goodness.

1604
01:22:35.076 --> 01:22:37.328
- There they are.
- I'm so happy they were able... Tig.

1605
01:22:37.412 --> 01:22:40.039
I'm so happy so many people
were able to come back.

1606
01:22:40.123 --> 01:22:42.917
I can't believe
everyone got up there for it.

1607
01:22:44.210 --> 01:22:45.378
Most of 'em.

1608
01:22:46.671 --> 01:22:48.840
And there's Wilson sort of.

1609
01:22:49.799 --> 01:22:51.885
Yeah. that's the cut-in.

1610
01:22:51.968 --> 01:22:53.845
Wait. was... Who else was there?

1611
01:22:53.928 --> 01:22:55.847
Was someone else not there that day?

1612
01:22:56.639 --> 01:22:58.016
No. Ronnie though.

1613
01:22:58.099 --> 01:23:01.269
Ronnie came back. which was exciting too.

1614
01:23:01.978 --> 01:23:06.691
Well. Hannah and Sara
weren't able to be there.

1615
01:23:06.774 --> 01:23:07.775
Yeah.

1616
01:23:08.818 --> 01:23:12.238
I love that we come out of that hug
with her and Tilly.

1617
01:23:12.322 --> 01:23:15.033
It's like a foundational relationship
on the show.

1618
01:23:16.993 --> 01:23:17.994
Yeah.

1619
01:23:28.129 --> 01:23:29.631
What was it like saying this?

1620
01:23:31.049 --> 01:23:33.051
Yeah. what was it like. Sonequa?

1621
01:23:34.427 --> 01:23:36.346
Y'all. it was so intense.

1622
01:23:41.476 --> 01:23:42.936
I love the way you delivered that.

1623
01:23:43.895 --> 01:23:45.563
- I just love it.
- Thank you.

1624
01:23:45.647 --> 01:23:49.275
It's like you were saying. Tunde.
man. there was just so much to feel.

1625
01:23:49.359 --> 01:23:51.110
We were feeling all the feels.

1626
01:23:51.194 --> 01:23:53.529
I mean.
we worked so hard those three days.

1627
01:23:53.613 --> 01:23:57.367
We were sleep deprived and delirious.
but we were just...

1628
01:23:57.450 --> 01:24:00.828
It's like I almost wouldn't have wanted it
to be any other kind of way.

1629
01:24:00.912 --> 01:24:02.121
you know what I'm saying?

1630
01:24:02.205 --> 01:24:05.750
Like. we gave our all there at the end.

1631
01:24:05.833 --> 01:24:10.964
and I wanted to encapsulate
every single moment

1632
01:24:11.047 --> 01:24:12.799
in that one "let's fly." right?

1633
01:24:12.882 --> 01:24:17.553
Which... That's impossible to do.
but that was the desire of my heart.

1634
01:24:18.179 --> 01:24:19.222
So it was quite intense.

1635
01:24:19.305 --> 01:24:21.516
I know we did a few takes.
I can't remember how many.

1636
01:24:21.599 --> 01:24:24.352
- And the spin out. you guys.
- Yeah.

1637
01:24:25.228 --> 01:24:26.354
Yeah.

1638
01:24:27.814 --> 01:24:29.315
- I'm gonna cry.
- I know!

1639
01:24:30.358 --> 01:24:33.695
Intense. It's intense. It's intense.

1640
01:24:35.029 --> 01:24:35.945
True.

1641
01:24:35.947 --> 01:24:37.699
I love y'all so much.

1642
01:24:37.782 --> 01:24:40.118
- Well done. Love you too. Love you all.
- I miss you guys.

1643
01:24:40.201 --> 01:24:42.829
- Yeah.
- I do. I miss y'all too.

1644
01:24:43.830 --> 01:24:46.207
- We just got to do it again. I guess.
- Yep.

1645
01:24:46.291 --> 01:24:47.667
- Yes. we do.
- It's done.

1646
01:25:31.669 --> 01:25:32.670
English (US)
